Session Note - March 18, 2026
Patient: Jennifer Walsh
Therapist: Dr. Michael Chen, PsyD

Presenting Concerns:
Patient originally presented with adjustment disorder related to divorce, now largely resolved. Severity is mild at this point. Concerns have been ongoing for eight months but symptoms have significantly decreased. No new concerns this session.

Session Summary:
Termination planning session. Reviewed progress made throughout 16 sessions of therapy. Patient reflected on gains in emotional regulation and boundary-setting skills. Discussed strategies for maintaining progress independently. Created relapse prevention plan identifying warning signs and coping strategies. Patient expressed gratitude and confidence about managing independently.

Mood Assessment:
Current mood: 8/10 (positive and confident)
Mood change from last session: Improved
Energy level: Normal
Emotional themes: gratitude, confidence, mild apprehension about ending therapy
Affect observed: Bright and engaged
Affect congruence: Congruent

Mental Status Examination:
Appearance: Well-groomed
Behavior: Cooperative and engaged
Speech: Normal
Thought process: Linear and organized
Thought content: Future-oriented, reflecting on progress
Perception: No abnormalities
Cognition: Intact
Insight: Good - clear understanding of gains and ongoing needs
Judgment: Good

Risk Assessment:
Suicidal ideation: None. Self-harm: None. Homicidal ideation: None. Risk level: Low.

Interventions Used:
- Relapse prevention planning
- Psychoeducation about maintaining gains
- Supportive therapy
Techniques were very effective - patient articulated clear plan for independence.
Skills practiced: Identifying warning signs, reviewing coping toolkit
Homework assigned: Implement relapse prevention plan and schedule follow-up if needed
Previous homework: Completed - practiced all assigned coping strategies successfully
Medications: Not applicable

Diagnoses:
Primary diagnosis: Adjustment Disorder with mixed anxiety and depressed mood, resolved
Primary diagnosis code: F43.23
Diagnosis status: Updated - symptoms have resolved

Treatment Progress:
Overall progress: Significant improvement across all treatment goals
Treatment phase: Termination
Barriers: Mild apprehension about ending therapy
Strengths: Strong coping skills, good social support network, self-awareness
Treatment goals: Emotional regulation, boundary setting, adjusting to post-divorce life
Goals addressed: All goals reviewed and progress consolidated

Plan:
- Final session - therapy concluded
- Discharge planned with option to return if needed
- No further regular sessions scheduled
- No referrals needed
- Level of care: Outpatient - completed
- Discharge planning: Ready for discharge
